          },
          "datePublished": "2023-04-25",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "4",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Went to a Christian wedding followed by the reception in this school. Parking was difficult because the playground isnt even. Had to park the car in a muddy place. Entrance has an 6 foot aquarium welcoming us.  The indoor playground is covered with ceiling and Kids can play without worrying about climate. There is a stage, flag pole, basketball net and two giant 15 foot ceiling fans inside the premises. Didnt check the classrooms since reception and dinner was arranged in ground floor. Restrooms could be maintained well. I see a all in one gym equipment in the play area(?). Not sure it was brought recently after school holidays have begun.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Christ Matric Higher Secondary School - Poonamallee"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Binuja S"
          },
          "datePublished": "2023-04-20",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I regret for admitting my children here. Not even a single teacher can speak one sentence in english. The teachers treat the students very harshly..my daughter is mentally traumatized by Suganthi 4th STD class teacher. she even shouted at my daughter in front of me and I felt disturbed by how the students are getting treated here. When I spoke to her I didn't understand a word she said , coz her English communication was pathetically poor. This is the reason my daughter couldn't understand her subject which is math's. I had to sit every day at home and teach her everything. I saw a complete degrade of my children's English communication, standard and cleanliness. Even after two years of being in this school, they cry every morning, I feel terrible for putting them here. I'm waiting for this academic year to be over so I can shift them to a better school with qualified teachers and a better management. One of the worst decisions I had taken.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        }
